WEBVTT

00:20.700 --> 00:25.520
CHAPTER I The vision of Isaiah, the son of Amoz, which

00:25.520 --> 00:32.880
concerning Judah and Jerusalem in the days of Uzziah, Jotham, Ahaz, and Hezekiah kings of Judah.

00:33.600 --> 00:41.500
Hear, O heavens, and give ear, O earth, for the Lord hath spoken. I have nourished and brought

00:41.500 --> 00:49.480
up children, and they have rebelled against me. The ox knoweth his owner, and the ass his master's

00:49.480 --> 00:59.260
crib, but Israel doth not know. My people doth not consider. Ah, sinful nation, a people laden with

00:59.260 --> 01:06.620
iniquity, a seed of evildoers, children that are corrupters. They have forsaken the Lord,

01:06.960 --> 01:13.040
they have provoked the Holy One of Israel unto anger. They are gone away backward.

01:13.900 --> 01:21.500
Why should ye be stricken any more? Ye will revolt more and more. The whole head is sick,

01:21.860 --> 01:28.860
and the whole heart faint. From the sole of the foot even unto the head there is no soundness in

01:28.860 --> 01:36.840
it but wounds, and bruises, and putrefying sores. They have not been closed, neither bound up,

01:36.840 --> 01:43.500
neither mollified with ointment. Your country is desolate, your cities are burned with fire,

01:43.800 --> 01:51.020
your land strangers devour it in your presence, and it is desolate as overthrown by strangers.

01:51.860 --> 01:58.440
And the daughter of Zion is left as a cottage in a vineyard, as a lodge in a garden of cucumbers,

01:59.320 --> 02:05.020
as a besieged city. Except the Lord of Host had left unto us a very small remnant,

02:05.020 --> 02:09.980
we should have been as Sodom, and we should have been like unto Gomorrah.

02:10.100 --> 02:16.000
Hear the word of the Lord, ye rulers of Sodom, give ear unto the law of our God, ye people of

02:16.000 --> 02:22.380
Gomorrah. To what purpose is the multitude of your sacrifices unto me, saith the Lord?

02:22.620 --> 02:29.560
I am full of the burnt offerings of rams, and the fat of fed beasts, and I delight not in the blood

02:29.560 --> 02:35.980
of bullocks, or of lambs, or of he-goats. When ye come to appear before me, who hath required

02:35.980 --> 02:45.560
this at your hand to tread my cords? Bring no more vain oblations. Incense is an abomination unto me.

02:45.880 --> 02:54.000
The new moons and Sabbaths, the calling of assemblies, I cannot away with. It is iniquity,

02:54.000 --> 03:01.800
even the solemn meeting. Your new moons and your appointed feasts my soul hateth.

03:02.260 --> 03:08.260
They are a trouble unto me. I am weary to bear them. And when ye spread forth your hands,

03:08.340 --> 03:16.720
I will hide mine eyes from you. Yea, when ye make many prayers, I will not hear. Your hands are full

03:16.720 --> 03:25.720
of blood. Wash you. Make you clean. Put away the evil of your doings, from before mine eyes cease

03:25.720 --> 03:34.040
to do evil. Learn to do well. Seek judgment. Relieve the oppressed. Judge the fatherless.

03:34.740 --> 03:42.260
Plead for the widow. Come now, let us reason together, saith the Lord. Though your sins be

03:42.260 --> 03:51.120
scarlet, they shall be as white as snow. Though they be red like crimson, they shall be as wool.

03:52.300 --> 04:00.360
If ye be willing and obedient, ye shall eat the good of the land. But if ye refuse and rebel,

04:01.240 --> 04:06.160
ye shall be devoured with the sword, for the mouth of the Lord hath spoken it.

04:06.960 --> 04:16.060
How is the faithful city becoming harlot? It was full of judgment. Righteousness lodged in it.

04:16.820 --> 04:25.340
But now murderers. Thy silver is become dross. Thy wine mixed with water. Thy princes are

04:25.340 --> 04:33.280
rebellious and companions of thieves. Everyone loveth gifts and followeth after rewards. They judge

04:33.280 --> 04:39.400
not the fatherless, neither doth the cause of the widow come unto them. Therefore saith the Lord,

04:39.580 --> 04:48.240
the Lord of hosts, the mighty one of Israel, I will ease me of mine adversaries, and avenge me

04:48.240 --> 04:57.480
of mine enemies. And I will turn my hand upon thee, and purely purge away thy dross, and take away all

04:57.480 --> 05:05.460
thy men. And I will restore thy judges as at the first, and thy counsellors as at the beginning.

05:06.000 --> 05:13.600
Afterward thou shalt be called the city of righteousness, the faithful city. Zion shall

05:13.600 --> 05:20.560
be redeemed with judgment, and her converts with righteousness. And the destruction of the transgressors

05:20.560 --> 05:26.740
and of the sinners shall be together. And they that forsake the Lord shall be consumed.

05:27.520 --> 05:34.900
For they shall be ashamed of the oaks which ye have desired, and ye shall be confounded for the

05:34.900 --> 05:43.540
gardens that ye have chosen. For ye shall be as an oak whose leaf fadeth, and as a garden that

05:43.540 --> 05:52.540
hath no water. And the strong shall be as toe, and the maker of it as a spark. And they shall

05:52.540 --> 06:01.780
both burn together, and none shall quench them. Chapter 2. The word that Isaiah the son of Amoz

06:01.780 --> 06:09.480
saw concerning Judah and Jerusalem. And it shall come to pass in the last days, that the mountain

06:09.480 --> 06:15.640
of the Lord's house shall be established in the top of the mountains, and shall be exalted above

06:15.640 --> 06:23.860
the hills, and all the nations shall flow unto it. And many people shall go, and say, Come ye,

06:24.180 --> 06:30.140
and let us go up to the mountain of the Lord, to the house of the God of Jacob. And he will teach

06:30.140 --> 06:38.460
us of his ways, and we will walk in his paths. For out of Zion shall go forth the law, and the

06:38.460 --> 06:45.620
word of the Lord from Jerusalem. And he shall judge among the nations, and shall rebuke many people.

06:45.640 --> 06:53.520
And they shall beat their swords into plowshares, and their spears into pruning-hooks. Nations shall

06:53.520 --> 07:01.920
not lift up sword against nation, neither shall they learn war any more. O house of Jacob, come ye,

07:02.420 --> 07:08.780
let us walk in the light of the Lord. Therefore thou hast forsaken thy people the house of Jacob,

07:08.780 --> 07:14.800
because they be replenished from the east, and are soothsayers like the Philistines,

07:15.220 --> 07:21.620
and they please themselves in the children of strangers. Their land also is full of silver and

07:21.620 --> 07:28.340
gold, neither is there any end of their treasures. Their land is also full of horses, neither is there

07:28.340 --> 07:35.560
any end of their chariots. Their land is also full of idols. They worship the work of their own hands,

07:35.560 --> 07:42.960
that which their own fingers have made. And the mean man boweth down, and the great man

07:42.960 --> 07:50.520
humbleth himself. Therefore forgive them not. Enter into the rock, and hide thee in the dust,

07:50.880 --> 07:57.780
for fear of the Lord, and for the glory of his majesty. The lofty looks of man shall be humbled,

07:58.480 --> 08:04.980
and the haughtiness of men shall be bowed down, and the Lord alone shall be exalted in that day.

08:05.560 --> 08:10.920
For the day of the Lord of hosts shall be upon every one that is proud and lofty,

08:11.780 --> 08:19.980
and upon every one that is lifted up, and he shall be brought low, and upon all the cedars of Lebanon

08:19.980 --> 08:27.080
that are high and lifted up, and upon all the oaks of Basian, and upon all the high mountains,

08:27.520 --> 08:34.740
and upon all the hills that are lifted up, and upon every high tower, and upon every fenced wall,

08:34.740 --> 08:40.580
and upon all the ships of Tarshish, and upon all pleasant pictures.

08:42.140 --> 08:48.180
And the loftiness of man shall be bowed down, and the haughtiness of men shall be made low,

08:49.060 --> 08:56.420
and the Lord alone shall be exalted in that day. And the idols he shall utterly abolish,

08:57.660 --> 09:02.800
and they shall go into the holes of the rocks, and into the caves of the earth,

09:02.800 --> 09:08.980
for fear of the Lord, and for the glory of his majesty, when he ariseth to shake terribly the

09:08.980 --> 09:16.860
earth. In that day a man shall cast his idols of silver, and his idols of gold, which they made

09:16.860 --> 09:24.340
each one for himself to worship, to the moles, and to the bats, to go into the clefts of the rocks,

09:24.900 --> 09:31.660
and into the tops of the ragged rocks, for fear of the Lord, and for the glory of his majesty,

09:31.660 --> 09:39.480
when he ariseth to shake terribly the earth. Cease ye from man, whose breath is in his nostrils,

09:40.000 --> 09:47.640
for wherein is he to be accounted of? Chapter 3 For behold, the Lord, the Lord of hosts,

09:47.880 --> 09:54.300
doth take away from Jerusalem, and from Judah, the stay, and the staff, the whole stay of bread,

09:54.580 --> 10:00.680
and the whole stay of water, the mighty man, and the man of war, the judge, and the prophet,

10:00.680 --> 10:06.880
and the prudent, and the ancient, the captain of fifty, and the honorable man, and the counselor,

10:07.360 --> 10:14.140
and the cunning artificer, and the eloquent orator, and I will give children to be their princes,

10:15.020 --> 10:21.160
and babes shall rule over them, and the people shall be oppressed every one by another,

10:21.540 --> 10:27.400
and every one by his neighbor, the child shall behave himself proudly against the ancient,

10:27.400 --> 10:34.200
and the base against the honorable. When a man shall take hold of his brother of the house of

10:34.200 --> 10:40.980
his father, saying, Thou hast clothing, be thou our ruler, and let this ruin be under thy hand.

10:41.560 --> 10:48.200
In that day shall he swear, saying, I will not be in healer, for in my house is neither bread,

10:48.320 --> 10:56.080
nor clothing, make me not a ruler of the people. For Jerusalem is ruined, and Judah has fallen,

10:56.080 --> 11:02.300
because their tongue and their doings are against the Lord, to provoke the eyes of his glory.

11:03.500 --> 11:09.160
The show of their countenance doth witness against them, and they declare their sin as

11:09.160 --> 11:16.180
sodom they hided not. Woe unto their soul, for they have rewarded evil unto themselves.

11:16.920 --> 11:22.320
Say ye to the righteous, that it shall be well with him, for they shall eat the fruit of their

11:22.320 --> 11:30.760
doings. Woe unto the wicked, it shall be ill with him, for the reward of his hands shall be given

11:30.760 --> 11:39.220
him. As for my people, children are their oppressors, and women rule over them. O my people,

11:39.940 --> 11:47.620
they which lead thee cause thee to err, and destroy the way of thy paths. The Lord standeth

11:47.620 --> 11:54.620
up to plead, and standeth to judge the people. The Lord will enter into judgment with the

11:54.620 --> 12:02.020
ancients of his people, and the princes thereof, for ye have eaten up the vineyard. The spoil of

12:02.020 --> 12:10.700
the poor is in your houses. What mean ye, that ye beat my people to pieces, and grind the faces

12:10.700 --> 12:17.600
of the poor, saith the Lord God of hosts? Moreover, the Lord saith, because the daughters of Zion are

12:17.600 --> 12:24.180
haughty, and walk with stretched forth necks and wanton eyes, walking and mincing as they go,

12:24.500 --> 12:30.880
and making a tinkling with their feet. Therefore the Lord will smite with a scab the crown of the

12:30.880 --> 12:38.240
head of the daughters of Zion, and the Lord will discover their secret paths. In that day, the Lord

12:38.240 --> 12:43.560
will take away the bravery of their tinkling ornaments about their feet, and their calls,

12:43.560 --> 12:49.080
and their round tires like the moon, the chains, and the bracelets, and the mufflers,

12:49.480 --> 12:54.740
the bonnets, and the ornaments of the legs, and the headbands, and the tablets, and the earrings,

12:55.080 --> 13:02.240
the rings, and the nose jewels, the changeable suits of apparel, and the mantles, and the wimples,

13:02.580 --> 13:10.160
and the crisping pins, the glasses, and the fine linen, and the hoods, and the veils.

13:10.160 --> 13:15.340
And it shall come to pass, that instead of sweet smell there shall be stink,

13:16.580 --> 13:23.460
and instead of a girdle a rent, and instead of well-set hair baldness, and instead of a

13:23.460 --> 13:32.140
stomacher a girding of sackcloth, and burning instead of beauty. Thy men shall fall by the sword,

13:32.140 --> 13:37.820
and thy mighty in the war, and her gates shall lament and mourn,

13:38.380 --> 13:42.060
and she being desolate shall sit upon the ground.

